
[1]revery

   REV'ERY, n.

   1. Properly, a raving or delirium; but its sense, as generally used, is
   a loose or irregular train of thoughts, occurring in musing or
   meditation; wild, extravagant conceit of the fancy or imagination.
   There are reveries and extravagancies which pass through the minds of
   wise men as well as fools.

   2. A chimera; a vision.
